168:     /// Loads settings, creating or repairing `settings.json` as needed.
169:     ///
170:     /// Missing files and malformed/non-object JSON reset to default settings and
171:     /// are saved immediately, matching the reference app's quiet first-run and
172:     /// recovery behavior. Syntactically valid objects preserve valid keys, repair
173:     /// invalid values, remove unknown keys on resave, and return diagnostics for
174:     /// later logging without surfacing UI errors.
